                "Tier 1: Slight enhancement, approximately 10% stronger barriers. <em>Your barriers survive a few extra melee strikes or glancing spell impacts before failing — enough to absorb an opportunistic cut that would have broken through before. The AGI begins monitoring for incoming attacks and suggests barrier activation when it detects imminent danger, shaving precious fractions off your defensive response time.</em>",
                "Tier 2: Moderate enhancement, approximately 25% stronger barriers. <em>Your barriers can withstand sustained melee pressure for several seconds before showing stress fractures — long enough to set a counter-attack. Low-tier offensive spells deflect harmlessly, and the barrier's regeneration cycle means minor damage from blade impacts repairs itself between strikes rather than accumulating toward failure.</em>",
