                "expert": "The Bombardment mage's targeting illusions approach the practical ceiling of artillery deception. Opponents cannot determine the mage's real position or predict where the next bombardment will land. The mage fights surrounded by a cloud of phantom firing signatures that make counter-battery effectively impossible to aim.\n\nThe substantial gains in artillery capability create momentum that is difficult to arrest. Each successful barrage in long-range fighting makes the next one easier, and the ranged specialist who seizes the initiative early controls the engagement from that point forward.",
                "master": "The targeting illusions operate at the spell's theoretical maximum for bombardment combat. The Bombardment mage projects a symphony of phantom firing positions that makes their real position completely unidentifiable. The mage is a phantom artillery platform — opponents cannot find them, cannot target them, and cannot escape their bombardment.\n\nThe transcendent improvement in phantom artillery that masks real firing positions and angles reshapes how the artillery mage approaches ranged combat. The ranged engagement shifts as the ranged specialist establishes fire-superiority that compounds with every volleys."
